Spec file for go

To create a source rpm, do the following:

- hg clone -u release https://go.googlecode.com/hg/ go
- modify the version number in the specfile to be somewhat correct
- tar zcvf golang-$VERSION.tar.gz go
- rpmbuild -bs --nodeps --define "_sourcedir ." --define "_srcrpmdir ." golang.spec

Then to create the binary, you can use rpmbuild or mock, mock would be better

Rpmbuild:
  rpmbuild --rebuild golang-$VERSION.src.rpm

Mock:
  sudo mock golang-$VERSION.src.rpm
